					<head>Divre ḥakhamim</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046" rend="visible">
						<summary>Sefer divre ḥakhamim, a collection of 416 short Talmudic and Midrashic expositions and comments by different writers, compiled by Yosef ben Shelomoh al-Sa'igh, who himself is the author of several of the pieces.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046">
							<locus from="1r" to="251v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer divre ḥakhamim </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר דברי חכמים</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en">al-Sa'igh, Yosef ben Shelomoh </persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he">אלסעיג, יוסף בן שלמה</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Folio 3r-6r give a numbered table of the contents of the manuscript, 416 in number.</p>
								<p>The name of the compiler frequently occurs at the end of the pieces under the designation המעתיק.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>251 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>210</height>
										<width>155</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>165</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>251 folios (+ 1 paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10-12 leaves each (irregular).</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>Several folios slightly mutilated.<p>Slightly stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="30" writtenLines="30">
									<p>Visible hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Various handwritings, approximately 10 or 12.</p>
									<p>Initial word of most of the section is written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Some additional comments are given in the outer margins.</p>
									<p>Watermarks of a scale inscribed in a circle, similar to Briquet no. 2584, <ref target="Briquet_1968" type="page">188</ref>, vol. 1.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="10">
							<summary>Sefardi cursive and semi-cursive scripts of the 17th century.<name type="person" role="scribe">Yosef ben Shelomoh al-Sa'igh</name>: inscribed throughout the manuscript, e.g. folio <locus n="7r"/>.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
